s\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 14865, \"end\": 14878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Felix\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Allyson Felix\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Felix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Felix\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fellow Olympic greats\", \"from\": 14795, \"to\": 14816}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 14883, \"to\": 14889}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medals\", \"from\": 14907, \"to\": 14918}, {\"ngram\": \"overall medals\", \"from\": 14923, \"to\": 14937}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles, 27, is already themost decorated Olympic gymnast in U.S. historywith eight total medals, five of them gold.\", \"from\": 14940, \"to\": 15054, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 14940, \"to\": 14945}, {\"ngram\": \"already themost decorated Olympic gymnast\", \"from\": 14954, \"to\": 14995}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S.\", \"from\": 14999, \"to\": 15003}, {\"ngram\": \"eight total medals\", \"from\": 15016, \"to\": 15034}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Really no one compares to Phelps, the retired swimming legend whose 23 gold medals and 28 total medals are both Olympic records for any athlete in any sport.\", \"from\": 15056, \"to\": 15213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15082, \"end\": 15088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 0.9999999677957027, \"rank\": 3.2141196320308255e-08, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 15063, \"to\": 15069}, {\"ngram\": \"the retired swimming legend\", \"from\": 15090, \"to\": 15117}, {\"ngram\": \"whose 23 gold medals\", \"from\": 15118, \"to\": 15138}, {\"ngram\": \"28 total medals\", \"from\": 15143, \"to\": 15158}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic records\", \"from\": 15168, \"to\": 15183}, {\"ngram\": \"any athlete\", \"from\": 15188, \"to\": 15199}, {\"ngram\": \"any sport\", \"from\": 15203, \"to\": 15212}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky, 27, now has eight gold medals and 12 medals overall afterwinning the 1,500-meter racelast night.\", \"from\": 15215, \"to\": 15320, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 15215, \"to\": 15222}, {\"ngram\": \"eight gold medals\", \"from\": 15236, \"to\": 15253}, {\"ngram\": \"12 medals\", \"from\": 15258, \"to\": 15267}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1,500-meter racelast night\", \"from\": 15289, \"to\": 15319}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is still competing in more events in Paris, so she could add to that total.\", \"from\": 15321, \"to\": 15400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15362, \"end\": 15367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999895177815287, \"rank\": 1.0482327678953672e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more events\", \"from\": 15347, \"to\": 15358}, {\"ngram\": \"that total\", \"from\": 15389, \"to\": 15399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Simone Biles is not too far behind Katie Ledecky when it comes to gold medals, despite having less chances to win them.\\u00c2Maddie Meyer / Getty Images Biles has a shot to reach nine career gold medals if she wins the all-around and the three upcoming individual events in which she qualified for the finals.\", \"from\": 15402, \"to\": 15707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15402, \"end\": 15414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 15437, \"end\": 15450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold medals\", \"from\": 15468, \"to\": 15479}, {\"ngram\": \"less chances\", \"from\": 15496, \"to\": 15508}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2Maddie Meyer / Getty Images Biles\", \"from\": 15521, \"to\": 15555}, {\"ngram\": \"a shot\", \"from\": 15560, \"to\": 15566}, {\"ngram\": \"nine career gold medals\", \"from\": 15576, \"to\": 15599}, {\"ngram\": \"the all-around\", \"from\": 15612, \"to\": 15626}, {\"ngram\": \"the three upcoming individual events\", \"from\": 15631, \"to\": 15667}, {\"ngram\": \"the finals\", \"from\": 15695, \"to\": 15705}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimmers have an advantage over gymnasts in that they have more chances to medal because they compete in relays and can qualify in numerous races.\", \"from\": 15709, \"to\": 15855, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Swimmers\", \"from\": 15709, \"to\": 15717}, {\"ngram\": \"an advantage\", \"from\": 15723, \"to\": 15735}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnasts\", \"from\": 15741, \"to\": 15749}, {\"ngram\": \"more chances\", \"from\": 15768, \"to\": 15780}, {\"ngram\": \"medal\", \"from\": 15784, \"to\": 15789}, {\"ngram\": \"relays\", \"from\": 15814, \"to\": 15820}, {\"ngram\": \"numerous races\", \"from\": 15840, \"to\": 15854}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The maximum number of medals a gymnast can win in one Games is six, whereas Phelps won eight gold medals at the 2008 Beijing Olympics alone.\", \"from\": 15856, \"to\": 15996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15932, \"end\": 15938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_S